# Copy project folder to VM via SCP
scp -r C:\Users\User\myproject root@192.168.56.110:/root/myproject
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Python, pip, virtualenv, Docker, and Nginx
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv docker.io nginx



1.3. Configure Virtual Environment
# Navigate to project folder
cd /root/myproject

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv .venv

# Activate virtual environment
source .venv/bin/activate      # Linux
# On Windows PowerShell: & .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps11.4. Install Python Dependencies
pip install flask pymysql redis deep-translator


1.4. Install Python Dependencies
pip install flask pymysql redis deep-translator


2.1. Install MySQL
sudo apt install -y mysql-server
sudo systemctl enable mysql
sudo systemctl start mysql


2.2. Configure Database
-- Log in as root
sudo mysql -u root

-- Create database
CREATE DATABASE translator_db;

-- Create user and grant privileges
CREATE USER 'translator_user'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'test1234';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON translator_db.* TO 'translator_user'@'%';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


2.3. Verify Remote Connection
mysql -h 192.168.56.109 -u translator_user -p translator_db



3.1. Install Redis
sudo apt install -y redis-server
sudo systemctl enable redis-server
sudo systemctl start redis-server


3.2. Secure Redis

Edit /etc/redis/redis.conf:

requirepass test1234


Restart Redis:

sudo systemctl restart redis-server

3.3. Test Redis
redis-cli -h 192.168.56.109 -a "test1234" ping
# Expected output: PONG

4. Flask App Configuration
4.1. app.py

MySQL & Redis credentials:

MYSQL_HOST = "192.168.56.109"
MYSQL_DB = "translator_db"
MYSQL_USER = "translator_user"
MYSQL_PASSWORD = "test1234"

REDIS_HOST = "192.168.56.109"
REDIS_PORT = 6379
REDIS_PASSWORD = "test1234"


Flask routes:

@app.route("/", methods=["GET", "POST"])
def translate():
    ...

4.2. HTML

templates/index.html:

<form method="POST">
    <textarea name="text" placeholder="Enter text"></textarea>
    <select name="direction">
        <option value="en_to_fr">English → French</option>
        <option value="fr_to_en">French → English</option>
    </select>
    <button type="submit">Translate</button>
</form>

5. Running the Application
5.1. Activate Virtual Environment
source .venv/bin/activate    # Linux
# On Windows PowerShell: & .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

5.2. Run Flask
python app.py


The server runs on http://0.0.0.0:5000

Access from host: http://<VM_IP>:5000

6. Verify Database & Redis
6.1. MySQL
SELECT * FROM translations;


Check that translations submitted via the web appear here.

6.2. Redis
redis-cli -h 192.168.56.109 -a "test1234"
GET total_translated_words
GET en_to_fr_count
GET fr_to_en_count


Verify counters are incrementing.

7. Optional: Nginx Setup
# Test Nginx
nginx -t
sudo systemctl restart nginx


Configure reverse proxy for Flask:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name <VM_IP>;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }
}

8. Troubleshooting
Issue	Fix
ModuleNotFoundError	Install missing package in .venv
Bad Request 400	Ensure form field names match Flask request.form.get("field")
MySQL Access Denied	Check username, host, password, and GRANT privileges
Redis Connection Refused	Check host, port, password, and firewall
